You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for extension operations.

EXTENSION COMMANDS
  create:      Create a new extension
  install:     Install a GitHub CLI extension
  list:        List installed extension commands
  remove:      Remove an installed extension
  upgrade:     Upgrade installed extensions


Note: These commands manage gh CLI extensions globally and do not require the --repo flag.
Extensions can be installed from GitHub repositories or local paths.
Use upgrade command to update all installed extensions.

Example usage:
- List extensions: GH_PAGER="" gh extension list
- Install extension: GH_PAGER="" gh extension install <repository>
- Remove extension: GH_PAGER="" gh extension remove <name>
- Upgrade extensions: GH_PAGER="" gh extension upgrade [name] 